OL,6,FIn his defence, jurors heard a series
OL,7,Fof glowing testimonials from
OL,8,Fcolleagues and senior officers.
OL,10,FDefence barrister Patrick Gibbs KC
OL,11,Ftold jurors: "He is not a robot, he is
OL,12,Fa human being with a human brain who
OL,13,Fdid this to the best of his ability."
OL,15,FA fellow firearms officer known as
OL,16,FDS87 said he would have taken a shot
OL,17,Fif Mr Blake had not, and another
OL,18,Freferred to as E156 said he was
OL,19,F"fractions of a second" away from
OL,20,Fdoing the same.
